ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, It's a great course because of the contents and nice professor
Enjoyed the course. I would recommend.

It is a good course for physical chemistry students that are interested in instrumental development and maintenance. It is also good for students that are interested in how the instrument actually works.
CHEM 560L is an important and useful class. Yes I would recommend it to other physical chemistry students, because it teaches you new techniques.
I would recommend it because it's good hands on training.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course covered some materials that usually aren't covered in other physical chemistry lab courses.
I learned many new techniques that will be useful in the future in my future research when I need to be handling and building equipment. It has deepened my understanding.
It will prepare me well for lab work
